comments.text: V32I is a non-polymorphic PI-selected mutation associated with reduced susceptibility to each of the PIs except SQV. It is included in the Tibotec DRV genotypic susceptibility score.
M46I/L are relatively non-polymorphic PI-selected mutations. In combination with other PI-resistance mutations, they are associated with reduced susceptibility to each of the PIs except DRV.
I47V is a non-polymorphic PI-selected mutation associated with reduced susceptibility to each of the PIs except SQV and ATV. I47V is included in the Tibotec DRV genotypic susceptibility score.
I50L is a non-polymorphic mutation selected by ATV. It causes high-level resistance to ATV and increases susceptibility to most of the remaining PIs.

V82T/S are non-polymorphic PI-selected mutations. They are associated with reduced susceptibility to each of the PIs except DRV. V82T is included in the Boehringer-Ingelheim TPV genotypic susceptibility score.
L90M is a non-polymorphic PI-selected mutation that reduces susceptibility to each of the PIs except TPV and DRV.
